modules.description: Provides functions to write to and read from the console, with support for both standard output and the PV console ring. Operates on byte sequences and character streams, handling input and output operations specific to Unix and Xen environments. Used to implement console logging and user interaction in system-level applications.

Provides functions to read from and write to a network flow, including handling disconnection, logging messages, and error reporting. Operates on buffer types from the Cstruct library and uses Lwt for asynchronous I/O. Supports writing multiple buffers at once, managing connection closure, and detecting end-of-file conditions during reads.
